byline.contributor: David Montgomery reported from Austin, and Katie Rogers from New York.
byline.original: By DAVID MONTGOMERY and KATIE ROGERS

abstract: Texas officials say traffic stop by local police in town southwest of Houston led to chase and subsequent crash that left six people dead;  sport utility vehicle, which was carrying 12 illegal immigrants, was driven by an American citizen and two other occupants of vehicle are believed to be members of smuggling organization.
lead_paragraph: Officials are investigating whether the more than dozen people in the vehicle that crashed were immigrants being transported by smugglers.

headline.main: Six People Killed in Texas as S.U.V. With Immigrants Wrecks While Fleeing Police
